<h2 id='sub-2-3' class='sec-h2'><span>2.3 Constraints</span></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>Type</strong></th>
<th><strong>Description</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td>The mobile application must work on both iOS and Android platforms</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td>Automated billing must run reliably on a monthly cycle without manual triggering</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td>Alerts must be delivered in a timely manner to be actionable</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td>The system must support French language for all user-facing interfaces given the business context</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td></td>
<td>Vehicle registration numbers must comply with local regulatory formats</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id='sub-2-4' class='sec-h2'><span>2.4 Assumptions</span></h2>
<p>- Each vehicle belongs to a single fleet managed by the same organization</p>
<p>- Drivers are employees or contractors who are registered in the system before using the mobile app</p>
<p>- Technical inspection (contrôle technique) renewal intervals follow standard regulatory requirements</p>
<p>- Monthly billing is based on calendar months</p>
<p>- The system will have an administrative back-office interface in addition to the mobile app for drivers</p>
<p>- Insurance and claims management does not replace the insurer's own system but tracks information internally</p>
<p>- Currency for all financial fields is assumed to be a single currency (EUR)</p>
<p>- Alert notifications may be delivered via email, push notification, or in-app notification — exact channel to be determined</p>
</section>
