<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Actor opens the Vehicle__c record whose status needs to change. <span class='dot'>·</span> Actor clicks 'Edit' or uses an inline edit on the Condition_Status__c field. <span class='dot'>·</span> Actor selects the new status value from the picklist (Available, Rented, In Maintenance, Out of Service). <span class='dot'>·</span> Actor clicks 'Save' to persist the status change. <span class='dot'>·</span> The system records the status change timestamp in Status_Last_Changed__c via automation.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-002-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Track Vehicle Status Change History</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A vehicle's Condition_Status__c is updated and the change must be logged for audit and tracking purposes.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• The system detects that Condition_Statusc has been changed on a Vehiclec record. <span class='dot'>·</span> The system automatically creates a Vehicle_Status_Historyc record linked to the Vehiclec. <span class='dot'>·</span> The history record captures Previous_Statusc, New_Statusc, Changed_Datec, and Changed_Byc. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Vehicle_Status_Historyc record is saved as a child of the Vehiclec record. <span class='dot'>·</span> Actor can view the full status history on the Vehicle__c record's related list.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-003' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-003'>
