<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-004'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-004-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Auto-Calculate Rental Contract Duration Based on Start and End Dates</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A Rental_Contractc record is created or the Start_Datec / End_Date__c is updated.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. The system detects that a Rental_Contract__c record has been created or its date fields have been modified. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. The system calculates the duration in months between Start_Datec and End_Datec. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. The system populates the Duration_Months__c formula field with the calculated value. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. The updated duration is displayed on the Rental Contract record detail page.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-004-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Automatically Determine and Update Rental Contract Status</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A Rental_Contract__c record is created, updated, or a scheduled daily process runs.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. The system evaluates the current date against the Start_Datec and End_Datec of each Rental_Contract__c record. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. If today's date is before Start_Datec, the system sets Statusc to 'Upcoming'. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. If today's date is between Start_Datec and End_Datec (inclusive), the system sets Status__c to 'Active'. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. If today's date is after End_Datec, the system sets Statusc to 'Expired'. <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. The system saves the updated Statusc on the Rental_Contractc record. <span class='dot'>·</span> 6. The scheduled flow repeats daily to keep all contract statuses current.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
