<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-013-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Associate Claim/Incident with Insurance Policy</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>User creates or edits a Claim/Incident record and needs to link it to the relevant insurance policy.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. User navigates to the Claim/Incident record (Claim__c). <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. User clicks Edit or opens the record in creation mode. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. User selects the relevant Insurance Policy from the Insurance_Policy__c lookup field. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. System validates that the selected policy is in Active status and covers the asset/contract related to the claim. <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. User saves the record. <span class='dot'>·</span> 6. System persists the association and displays the linked policy details on the Claim record.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-013-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Track Insurance Coverage Utilization per Policy</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A Claim/Incident record is saved with an associated Insurance Policy, and the system needs to update coverage utilization metrics.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. System detects that a Claimc record has been created or updated with an Insurance_Policyc association. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. System calculates the total number of claims and total claimed amount for the associated policy. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. System updates the Total_Claims_Countc and Total_Claimed_Amountc rollup fields on the Insurance_Policy__c record. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. If Total_Claimed_Amountc exceeds the Coverage_Limitc, system flags the policy with a Coverage_Limit_Exceeded__c checkbox. <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. System sends a notification to the policy manager if the coverage limit is exceeded.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-014' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-014'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-014</strong></td>
<td><strong>2</strong></td>
<td>UC-014-01, UC-014-02</td>
<td>System (Scheduled Process), System</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-014'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-014-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Automatically Generate Monthly Invoices for Active Rental Contracts</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System (Scheduled Process)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Scheduled job runs on the 1st of each month to identify all active rental contracts and generate invoices.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. Scheduled Flow executes on the 1st of each month at a configured time. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. System queries all Rental_Contractc records where Contract_Statusc = 'Active' and Contract_Start_Date__c &lt;= TODAY. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. For each active contract, system creates an Invoicec record with Invoice_Amountc set to the contract's Monthly_Rate__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. System populates Invoice_Datec as the 1st of the current month, Due_Datec as 30 days from Invoice_Datec, and Invoice_Statusc as 'Pending'. <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. System associates the Invoicec with the Rental_Contractc and the related Account__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> 6. System sends an email notification to the tenant/account contact with the invoice details.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-014-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Validate Invoice Generation Against Contract Terms</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>An Invoicec record is created (either manually or by the scheduled process) linked to a Rental_Contractc.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. System detects an Invoicec record is being inserted with a Rental_Contractc lookup populated. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. System retrieves the associated Rental_Contractc and checks Contract_Statusc is 'Active'. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. System validates that Invoice_Amountc matches the Monthly_Ratec on the contract (or is a valid prorated amount). <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. System validates that no other Invoicec exists for the same Rental_Contractc and Billing_Period__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. If any validation fails, system prevents the save and displays the appropriate error message.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-015' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-015'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-015</strong></td>
<td><strong>3</strong></td>
<td>UC-015-01, UC-015-02, UC-015-03</td>
<td>System Administrator, Finance Staff, System (Automated Process)</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-015'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-015-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Configure Invoice Payment Status Data Model</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System Administrator</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Initial system setup or configuration change request for invoice payment tracking</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Admin navigates to Object Manager and selects the Invoice__c custom object. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin creates a picklist field Payment_Status__c with values: Unpaid, Paid, Partially Paid, Overdue. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin sets the default value of Payment_Status__c to Unpaid. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin creates a currency field Amount_Paid__c to track partial payments. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin adds Payment_Statusc and Amount_Paidc to the Invoice page layout and assigns field-level security for the Finance profile. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin verifies the fields are visible and editable for finance staff.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-015-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Finance Staff Updates Invoice Payment Status</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Finance Staff</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Finance staff receives a payment or identifies an overdue invoice and needs to update the payment status</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Finance user navigates to the Invoice__c record. <span class='dot'>·</span> Finance user clicks Edit and selects the appropriate Payment_Status__c value (Paid, Partially Paid, or Overdue). <span class='dot'>·</span> If Partially Paid is selected, the user enters the Amount_Paid__c value. <span class='dot'>·</span> Finance user saves the record. <span class='dot'>·</span> System validates that Amount_Paidc is less than Total_Amountc when status is Partially Paid. <span class='dot'>·</span> System saves the record and displays the updated payment status.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-015-03</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Automatically Flag Overdue Invoices</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System (Automated Process)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Scheduled daily evaluation of invoices where Due_Datec has passed and Payment_Statusc is Unpaid or Partially Paid</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• A scheduled Flow runs daily at a configured time. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Flow queries all Invoicec records where Due_Datec is before today and Payment_Status__c is Unpaid or Partially Paid. <span class='dot'>·</span> For each qualifying record, the Flow updates Payment_Status__c to Overdue. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Flow logs the number of records updated for audit purposes. <span class='dot'>·</span> Finance staff can view updated overdue invoices via a list view or report.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-016' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-016'>
