<td>Driver, System Administrator, System (Automated Process)</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-016'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-016-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Driver Submits Vehicle Problem or Incident Report via Mobile</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Driver</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Driver encounters a vehicle problem or incident and opens the mobile application to report it</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Driver opens the Salesforce Mobile App and navigates to the New Incident Report action. <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver selects the Report_Typec (Vehicle Problem or Incident) and the associated Vehiclec lookup. <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver enters a Description__c of the problem or incident in the text area field. <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver optionally attaches a photo using the device camera or gallery, which is stored as a ContentVersion file. <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver taps Submit, and the system creates an Incident_Reportc record with Statusc set to Submitted and Reported_DateTime__c set to the current timestamp. <span class='dot'>·</span> System displays a confirmation message with the Incident_Report__c record number.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-016-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Configure Mobile-Optimized Incident Report Page Layout and Action</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System Administrator</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>System setup to enable mobile incident reporting for drivers</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Admin creates the Incident_Reportc custom object with fields: Report_Typec (picklist), Vehiclec (lookup), Descriptionc (long text area), Statusc (picklist), Reported_DateTimec (datetime), Driver__c (lookup to User). <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin creates a compact layout for Incident_Reportc optimized for mobile display showing Report_Typec, Vehiclec, Statusc, and Reported_DateTime__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin creates a global quick action 'Report Incident' with a mobile-friendly layout including Report_Typec, Vehiclec, Description__c, and a file upload component. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin adds the quick action to the Salesforce Mobile App navigation and the Publisher Layout. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin assigns object permissions and field-level security so drivers can create and view Incident_Report__c records but not edit after submission. <span class='dot'>·</span> Admin tests the action on the Salesforce Mobile App to verify usability.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-016-03</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Notify Fleet Manager Upon New Incident Report Submission</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System (Automated Process)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A new Incident_Reportc record is created with Statusc equal to Submitted</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• A record-triggered Flow fires when an Incident_Reportc record is created with Statusc = Submitted. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Flow retrieves the Fleet Manager user associated with the Vehiclec record via Vehiclec.Fleet_Manager__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Flow sends an email notification to the Fleet Manager with incident details including Report_Typec, Vehiclec name, Description__c, and a link to the record. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Flow creates a Task assigned to the Fleet Manager to review the incident report with a due date of one business day.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-017' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-017'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-017</strong></td>
<td><strong>2</strong></td>
<td>UC-017-01, UC-017-02</td>
<td>Driver (Business User), System</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-017'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-017-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Submit Mileage Reading via Mobile Application</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Driver (Business User)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Driver opens the mobile app and selects the mileage submission option for their assigned vehicle.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. Driver logs into the mobile application and navigates to the Mileage Submission screen. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. System auto-populates the driver's assigned vehicle (Vehiclec) based on the active Driver_Vehicle_Assignmentc record. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. Driver enters the current mileage reading and optionally adds a photo of the odometer. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. Driver taps Submit to create a new Mileage_Reading__c record. <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. System validates that the submitted mileage is greater than the vehicle's last recorded mileage. <span class='dot'>·</span> 6. System updates the Current_Mileagec field on the Vehiclec record and confirms submission to the driver.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-017-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Validate Mileage Reading Value on Submission</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A new Mileage_Reading__c record is created or updated.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. System retrieves the related Vehiclec record via the Vehiclec lookup on Mileage_Reading__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. System compares Reading_Valuec against Vehiclec.Current_Mileage__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. If Reading_Valuec is less than or equal to Current_Mileagec, system blocks the save with a validation error. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. If Reading_Value__c is valid, the record is saved successfully.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-018' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-018'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-018</strong></td>
<td><strong>2</strong></td>
<td>UC-018-01, UC-018-02</td>
<td>Fleet Manager (Business User), System</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-018'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-018-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Create and Manage Driver-to-Vehicle Assignment</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Fleet Manager (Business User)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Fleet Manager needs to assign a driver to a vehicle or update an existing assignment.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. Fleet Manager navigates to the Driver_Vehicle_Assignment__c object and clicks New. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. Fleet Manager selects the Driverc (lookup to Contact or User) and Vehiclec (lookup to Vehicle__c). <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. Fleet Manager sets the Assignment_Start_Datec and optionally the Assignment_End_Datec. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. System validates that the vehicle does not already have another active assignment (no overlapping date ranges). <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. System validates that the driver does not already have another active vehicle assignment. <span class='dot'>·</span> 6. System saves the record and sets Status__c to 'Active'.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-018-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Enforce Unique Active Assignment per Vehicle and Driver</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A Driver_Vehicle_Assignmentc record is created or updated with Statusc = 'Active'.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• 1. System queries existing Driver_Vehicle_Assignmentc records where Vehiclec matches and Status__c = 'Active' and Id != current record Id. <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. If a matching active record exists for the same vehicle, system blocks the save. <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. System queries existing Driver_Vehicle_Assignmentc records where Driverc matches and Status__c = 'Active' and Id != current record Id. <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. If a matching active record exists for the same driver, system blocks the save. <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. If no conflicts are found, the record is saved successfully.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-019' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-019'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-019</strong></td>
<td><strong>2</strong></td>
<td>UC-019-01, UC-019-02</td>
<td>Business User, System (Scheduled Process)</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-019'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-019-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Display Fleet Overview Dashboard with Key Metrics</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>User navigates to the Fleet Management Dashboard</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• System loads the Fleet Overview Dashboard page <span class='dot'>·</span> System queries Vehicle__c records and displays total vehicle count <span class='dot'>·</span> System groups and displays vehicles by Status__c (Active, In Maintenance, Decommissioned, etc.) in a donut chart <span class='dot'>·</span> System queries Maintenancec records where Scheduled_Datec is within the next 30 days and displays upcoming maintenance count and list <span class='dot'>·</span> System queries Contractc records where End_Datec is within the next 60 days and displays expiring contracts <span class='dot'>·</span> System queries Claimc records where Statusc = 'Open' and Invoicec records where Due_Datec &lt; TODAY and Status__c != 'Paid', displaying counts for each</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-019-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Auto-Refresh Dashboard Metrics via Scheduled Data Aggregation</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System (Scheduled Process)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Scheduled job runs daily at a configured time (e.g., 6:00 AM)</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Scheduled Flow executes and queries all Vehiclec records, aggregating total count and count by Statusc <span class='dot'>·</span> Flow queries Maintenancec where Scheduled_Datec &gt;= TODAY and Scheduled_Datec &lt;= NEXT 30 DAYS, storing the count in Fleet_Metricc record <span class='dot'>·</span> Flow queries Contract records where EndDate &lt;= NEXT 60 DAYS and Status = 'Activated', storing count in Fleet_Metric__c <span class='dot'>·</span> Flow queries Claimc where Statusc = 'Open' and Invoicec where Due_Datec &lt; TODAY and Status__c != 'Paid', storing counts <span class='dot'>·</span> Flow upserts a Fleet_Metricc snapshot record with all aggregated values and Snapshot_Datec = TODAY <span class='dot'>·</span> Dashboard components reference Fleet_Metric__c for fast rendering without real-time SOQL overhead</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-020' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-020'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-020</strong></td>
<td><strong>3</strong></td>
<td>UC-020-01, UC-020-02, UC-020-03</td>
<td>Business User, System (Automated Process)</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-020'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-020-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Log Maintenance Cost on Each Maintenance Record Linked to a Vehicle</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>User creates or updates a Maintenance__c record with cost information</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• User opens a Vehicle__c record and clicks 'New Maintenance' from the related list <span class='dot'>·</span> User fills in Maintenance_Typec, Scheduled_Datec, Completion_Datec, and Costc (currency field) <span class='dot'>·</span> User optionally adds line-item details in Descriptionc and selects Service_Providerc <span class='dot'>·</span> User saves the Maintenance__c record <span class='dot'>·</span> Validation rule ensures Costc is greater than or equal to 0 and Vehiclec lookup is populated <span class='dot'>·</span> Record is saved and appears in the Vehicle's Maintenance related list</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-020-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Aggregate Total Maintenance Cost on Vehicle Record</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System (Automated Process)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A Maintenancec record is created, updated (Costc changed), or deleted</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Record-triggered Flow fires after insert, update, or delete on Maintenance__c <span class='dot'>·</span> Flow retrieves all Maintenancec records related to the parent Vehiclec <span class='dot'>·</span> Flow calculates the sum of Costc across all related Maintenancec records <span class='dot'>·</span> Flow updates Vehiclec.Total_Maintenance_Costc with the aggregated sum <span class='dot'>·</span> Vehicle__c record reflects the updated total maintenance cost immediately</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-020-03</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Generate Fleet Cost Analysis Report for Vehicle Lifecycle Decisions</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>User navigates to the Fleet Cost Analysis report or report tab</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• User opens the 'Fleet Cost Analysis' custom report type based on Vehiclec with Maintenancec child records <span class='dot'>·</span> Report displays each Vehiclec with Name, Yearc, Mileagec, Statusc, Total_Maintenance_Costc, and Purchase_Datec <span class='dot'>·</span> User applies filters such as date range, vehicle status, or cost threshold to narrow results <span class='dot'>·</span> Report calculates average maintenance cost per vehicle and highlights vehicles exceeding a cost threshold <span class='dot'>·</span> User exports or saves the report for lifecycle decision-making (e.g., identifying vehicles for replacement)</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-021' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-021'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-021</strong></td>
<td><strong>2</strong></td>
<td>UC-021-01, UC-021-02</td>
<td>System Administrator, Automated System Process</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-021'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-021-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Configure Alert Lead Time Settings per Alert Type</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System Administrator</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Administrator navigates to the Alert Configuration settings to define or update lead time values for automatic alerts.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Administrator opens the Alert Configuration custom settings or custom metadata type (Alert_Configuration__mdt). <span class='dot'>·</span> System displays existing alert type records (Technical Inspection, Maintenance, Contract End) with their current lead time values. <span class='dot'>·</span> Administrator selects an alert type record to edit. <span class='dot'>·</span> Administrator enters or modifies the Lead_Time_Days__c value (number of days in advance). <span class='dot'>·</span> Administrator clicks Save. <span class='dot'>·</span> System validates the input and persists the updated lead time configuration.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-021-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Apply Configured Lead Times to Scheduled Alert Generation</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Automated System Process</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A scheduled process runs daily to evaluate upcoming events against configured lead times and generate alerts.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Scheduled Flow executes at the configured daily time. <span class='dot'>·</span> System retrieves all active Alert_Configurationmdt records with their Lead_Time_Daysc values. <span class='dot'>·</span> For each alert type, system queries Vehicle__c and related records (e.g., next inspection date, next maintenance date, contract end date) where the event date minus lead time days equals today or falls within the alert window. <span class='dot'>·</span> System creates Alert__c records for each matching vehicle-event combination that does not already have an open alert. <span class='dot'>·</span> System sends notifications to assigned fleet managers or vehicle owners. <span class='dot'>·</span> System logs the alert generation results for audit purposes.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-022' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-022'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-022</strong></td>
<td><strong>3</strong></td>
<td>UC-022-01, UC-022-02, UC-022-03</td>
<td>Business User, Automated System Process</td>
</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-022'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-022-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Record Mileage Reading for a Vehicle</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>User records a new mileage reading for a vehicle (manual entry or integration update).</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• User navigates to the Vehiclec record and clicks 'New Mileage Reading' on the Mileage_Readingc related list. <span class='dot'>·</span> System displays the mileage reading entry form with fields: Reading_Datec, Odometer_Valuec, Source__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> User enters the odometer value and reading date. <span class='dot'>·</span> System validates that the new odometer value is greater than or equal to the most recent prior reading for the same vehicle. <span class='dot'>·</span> System saves the Mileage_Readingc record and updates the Vehiclec.Current_Mileagec and Vehiclec.Last_Mileage_Date__c fields. <span class='dot'>·</span> System recalculates the Vehiclec.Average_Daily_Mileagec based on the full reading history.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-022-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Detect Mileage Anomalies Based on Historical Trends</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Automated System Process</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A new Mileage_Reading__c record is created for a vehicle.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• System retrieves the last 10 mileage readings for the vehicle to calculate the historical average daily mileage and standard deviation. <span class='dot'>·</span> System computes the daily mileage rate for the new reading based on the difference from the prior reading divided by elapsed days. <span class='dot'>·</span> System compares the new daily rate against the historical average; if it exceeds 2x the standard deviation, it is flagged as anomalous. <span class='dot'>·</span> System sets Mileage_Readingc.Is_Anomalyc to true and populates Mileage_Readingc.Anomaly_Reasonc with the deviation details. <span class='dot'>·</span> System creates a Task assigned to the Fleet Manager with subject 'Mileage Anomaly Detected' linked to the Vehicle__c record. <span class='dot'>·</span> System updates Vehiclec.Has_Mileage_Anomalyc to true.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-022-03</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>View Mileage History and Trend Analysis for a Vehicle</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Business User</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>User navigates to the Mileage History tab or related list on a Vehicle__c record to review historical mileage data.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• User opens the Vehicle__c record and selects the 'Mileage History' tab or related list. <span class='dot'>·</span> System displays all Mileage_Readingc records in chronological order with columns: Reading_Datec, Odometer_Valuec, Daily_Mileage_Ratec, Is_Anomalyc, Sourcec. <span class='dot'>·</span> User can filter readings by date range, source, or anomaly status. <span class='dot'>·</span> System displays a mileage trend chart showing odometer progression over time with anomaly points highlighted. <span class='dot'>·</span> User can export the mileage history data to CSV for external analysis.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
