</tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-023'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-023-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Submit Problem Report from Mobile App</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Driver</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Driver encounters a vehicle issue and opens the mobile app to submit a problem report.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Driver navigates to the Problem Report submission screen in the mobile app. <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver selects the vehicle from their assigned vehicle list and chooses a problem category from a picklist (e.g., Mechanical, Electrical, Body Damage, Safety). <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver enters a description of the problem and optionally attaches photos. <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver submits the problem report, which creates a Problem_Reportc record with Statusc set to 'New'. <span class='dot'>·</span> System sends a confirmation notification to the driver and a new report notification to the Fleet Management queue. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Problem_Report__c record appears on the Fleet Management dashboard for review.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-023-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Review and Assign Problem Report to Technician</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Fleet Manager</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Fleet Manager reviews a newly submitted problem report and assigns it for resolution.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Fleet Manager opens the Problem_Reportc list view filtered by Statusc = 'New'. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager opens a specific Problem_Report__c record and reviews the details, photos, and vehicle history. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager sets the Priority__c field (Low, Medium, High, Critical) based on the reported issue. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager assigns the report to a technician or service provider by populating the Assigned_To__c lookup field. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager updates the Statusc to 'Assigned' and adds any internal notes in Resolution_Notesc. <span class='dot'>·</span> System sends a task notification to the assigned technician with the problem report details.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-023-03</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Track and Close Problem Report Resolution</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Fleet Manager</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Assigned technician completes the repair and the fleet manager verifies and closes the problem report.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Assigned technician updates the Problem_Reportc record with resolution details in Resolution_Notesc and sets Status__c to 'Resolved'. <span class='dot'>·</span> System records the Resolution_Datec as the current date/time and calculates Resolution_Time_Hoursc from Submitted_Date__c. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager receives a notification that the report has been marked as 'Resolved'. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager reviews the resolution details and confirms the fix by updating Status__c to 'Closed'. <span class='dot'>·</span> System updates the Vehiclec record's Last_Service_Datec field with the resolution date. <span class='dot'>·</span> Driver receives a notification that their reported problem has been resolved and closed.</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
<tr class='tbl-row-summary' data-id='BR-024' tabindex='0' role='button' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='detail-uc_index-BR-024'>
<td class='tbl-toggle'><span class='tbl-caret'></span></td>
<td><strong>BR-024</strong></td>
