<tr class='tbl-row-detail' id='detail-uc_index-BR-024'><td colspan='5'><div class='tbl-detail-body uc-cards'>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-024-01</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Generate Insurance Expiration Alert at Configurable Thresholds</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>System (Automated)</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>A scheduled daily process evaluates all active vehicle insurance policies and generates alerts for those approaching expiration.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• A scheduled Flow runs daily and queries all Vehicle_Insurancec records where Policy_Statusc = 'Active' and Expiration_Date__c is within the configured alert thresholds (60, 30, 14, and 7 days). <span class='dot'>·</span> For each qualifying record, the system creates an Insurance_Alertc record with Alert_Typec indicating the threshold (e.g., '30-Day Warning') and links it to the Vehiclec and Vehicle_Insurancec. <span class='dot'>·</span> System checks for existing open alerts on the same policy at the same threshold to prevent duplicate alerts. <span class='dot'>·</span> System sends an email notification to the Fleet Manager and the vehicle's assigned driver with the policy details and days remaining. <span class='dot'>·</span> The Insurance_Alert__c record is added to the Fleet Management dashboard under 'Upcoming Expirations' with a color-coded urgency indicator. <span class='dot'>·</span> System logs the alert generation timestamp in Alert_Generated_Date__c for audit purposes.</dd>
</dl></div>
<div class='uc-card'>
<div class='uc-card-head'>
<span class='req-code uc'>UC-024-02</span>
<span class='uc-card-title'>Acknowledge and Act on Insurance Expiration Alert</span>
</div>
<dl class='detail-kv'>
<dt>Actor</dt><dd>Fleet Manager</dd>
<dt>Trigger</dt><dd>Fleet Manager receives an insurance expiration alert notification and takes action to renew or address the expiring policy.</dd>
<dt>Main Flow</dt><dd>• Fleet Manager opens the Insurance_Alert__c record from the dashboard or email notification link. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager reviews the policy details including Vehiclec, Policy_Numberc, Expiration_Datec, and Days_Until_Expirationc. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager acknowledges the alert by updating Alert_Statusc from 'Open' to 'Acknowledged' and records any action notes in Action_Notesc. <span class='dot'>·</span> Fleet Manager initiates the renewal process by creating or updating the Vehicle_Insurance__c record with the new policy details. <span class='dot'>·</span> Upon successful renewal (Policy_Statusc updated to 'Active' with a future Expiration_Datec), the Insurance_Alertc.Alert_Statusc is automatically set to 'Resolved'. <span class='dot'>·</span> ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────</dd>
</dl></div>
</div></td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</section>
