<h3 class='sec-h3'>Integration points</h3>
<p>- Salesforce Mobile App</p>
<h3 class='sec-h3'>Security requirements</h3>
<p>- Role-based access: Finance Staff profile for Invoice Payment_Status__c editing (BR-015)</p>
<p>- Field-level security: Payment_Status__c read-only for non-finance users (BR-015)</p>
<p>- Object/field-level security: Drivers cannot edit submitted Incident_Report__c records (BR-016)</p>
<p>- Record owner-based fallback for notifications when manager fields are blank (BR-009, BR-010, BR-016)</p>
<p>- Fleet Manager role required for problem report assignment and closure (BR-023)</p>
<p>- System Administrator access for Custom Metadata Type configuration (BR-009, BR-021)</p>
<p>- Profile-based access to Fleet Overview Dashboard (BR-019)</p>
<h2 id='sub-4-3' class='sec-h2'><span>4.3 Recommendations to Architect</span></h2>
<p>- CRITICAL: Consolidate Maintenancec and Maintenance_Activityc into a single object — BR-006, BR-019, and BR-020 reference overlapping maintenance concepts with different object names. Recommend using Maintenance_Activity__c as the canonical object.</p>
<p>- CRITICAL: Clarify and consolidate the Client data model — BR-005 uses Clientc while BR-003 uses Account as the client entity. Determine whether to use standard Account/Contact or custom Clientc and standardize across all use cases.</p>
<p>- CRITICAL: Consolidate Sinistrec (BR-011) and Claimc (BR-013) — these appear to represent the same concept (insurance claims/incidents). Recommend a single object with Incident_Type__c to differentiate.</p>
<p>- CRITICAL: Consolidate Insurance_Policyc (BR-012) and Vehicle_Insurancec (BR-024) — these represent the same insurance policy concept. Use a single object.</p>
<p>- CRITICAL: Consolidate alert objects — Inspection_Alertc (BR-008), Insurance_Alertc (BR-024), and Alertc (BR-021) could be unified into a single Alertc object with Alert_Type__c picklist to reduce object sprawl.</p>
<p>- CRITICAL: Consolidate Maintenance_Alert_Settingmdt (BR-009) and Alert_Configurationmdt (BR-021) into a single Custom Metadata Type for all alert threshold configurations.</p>
<p>- CRITICAL: Consolidate Mileage_Readingc field naming — BR-017 uses Reading_Valuec while BR-022 uses Odometer_Value__c for the same concept. Standardize field names.</p>
<p>- Consider using Roll-Up Summary fields (if Master-Detail) or Rollup Helper/DLRS instead of Flow-based aggregation for Total_Maintenance_Costc (BR-020) and Total_Claims_Countc/Total_Claimed_Amount__c (BR-013) for better performance.</p>
<p>- Use Formula Fields for calculated values where possible: Duration_Monthsc (BR-004), Next_Inspection_Due_Datec (BR-008) to avoid automation overhead.</p>
<p>- Implement a unified Scheduled Flow architecture — multiple BRs require daily scheduled processes (BR-004, BR-008, BR-009, BR-010, BR-012, BR-015, BR-019, BR-021, BR-024). Consider a single orchestrator flow or batch Apex to reduce scheduled job count and improve maintainability.</p>
<p>- Use Master-Detail relationships where appropriate: Maintenance_Activityc to Vehiclec, Vehicle_Status_Historyc to Vehiclec, Invoicec to Rental_Contractc — this enables native Roll-Up Summary fields.</p>
<p>- Implement duplicate rules and matching rules for Registration_Numberc (BR-001), National_IDc (BR-005), and Policy_Number__c (BR-012) instead of or in addition to validation rules.</p>
<p>- For the Apex trigger enforcing unique active assignments (BR-018), ensure bulkification and consider using a unique compound index via a concatenated unique text field (Vehicle__c + Status Active) as an alternative.</p>
<p>- For mileage anomaly detection (BR-022), Apex is appropriate due to the computational complexity of historical trend analysis. Ensure the trigger is bulkified.</p>
<p>- Consider Platform Events or Custom Notifications for real-time alert delivery instead of relying solely on email and Task creation.</p>
<p>- Implement a consistent notification framework across all alert types (maintenance, inspection, insurance, contract expiration) to reduce code duplication.</p>
<p>- For the Fleet Overview Dashboard (BR-019), consider using standard Salesforce Reports and Dashboards with real-time data rather than a separate Fleet_Metric__c snapshot object, unless historical trend analysis of metrics is required.</p>
<p>- Ensure all scheduled flows have proper error handling, logging, and retry mechanisms to handle bulk data processing failures.</p>
<p>- Consider using Salesforce Mobile Publisher or a custom LWC for the mobile incident/problem reporting screens (BR-016, BR-023) to provide a better user experience than standard quick actions.</p>
