<h2 id='sub-7-3' class='sec-h2'><span>7.3 Migration Considerations</span></h2>
<p>- This is a greenfield implementation - no data migration from existing Salesforce objects is required, but initial data seeding of 150 vehicles and associated client/driver records must be planned.</p>
<p>- Customer Community Plus licenses must be procured for driver users before Experience Cloud configuration can begin.</p>
<p>- Custom metadata records (Alert_Configurationmdt, Maintenance_Alert_Settingmdt) must be deployed with initial configuration values as part of the metadata deployment, not as data migration.</p>
<p>- All 9 scheduled flows must be activated in sequence after deployment, with staggered execution times (1:00 AM through 7:15 AM) to avoid concurrent governor limit issues.</p>
<p>- Field history tracking must be enabled on Sinistrec.Resolution_Statusc before the incidentTimeline LWC can function correctly.</p>
<p>- The Monthly Invoice Generation scheduled flow should not be activated until after initial rental contract data is loaded and validated to prevent premature invoice creation.</p>
<p>- Chart.js or equivalent charting library must be uploaded as a static resource for the vehicleMileageTrend LWC component.</p>
<h2 id='sub-7-4' class='sec-h2'><span>7.4 Risk Areas</span></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>Risk area</strong></th>
<th><strong>Severity</strong></th>
<th><strong>Description / mitigation</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>High volume of scheduled flows (9 daily jobs) running against growing data volumes could hit governor limits as fleet scales beyond 150 vehicles. Batch Apex fallback implementations should be planned for the most data-intensive flows (invoice generation, fleet metrics snapshot).</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Race condition risk on Driver_Vehicle_Assignment__c despite Apex trigger protection - concurrent API operations could still create edge cases. Nightly reconciliation batch job recommended.</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Monthly invoice generation has duplicate creation risk if flow fails mid-execution and is retried. The combination of Billing_Period__c duplicate check in flow and InvoiceValidationTrigger provides defense-in-depth but should be monitored closely.</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Mileage anomaly detection (2x average threshold) may generate false positives for vehicles with irregular usage patterns, creating unnecessary fleet manager workload. Threshold should be configurable via custom metadata.</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Mobile LWC components depend on reliable network connectivity for file uploads (incident photos, odometer photos). Client-side image compression and offline capability should be considered.</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>The alertConfigurationManager LWC uses Metadata API for saving custom metadata, which requires specific permissions and may have deployment delays. Alternative approach of direct Setup navigation should be available as fallback.</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Complex interdependencies between flows on the same objects (e.g., multiple flows on Maintenance_Activityc and Vehiclec) create recursion risk. Static Boolean flags and careful entry condition design are critical.</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Customer Community Plus licensing costs and Experience Cloud setup complexity could impact timeline and budget for driver mobile access.</strong></td>
<td><strong>—</strong></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</section>
