<h2 id='sub-9-6' class='sec-h2'><span>9.6 Validation Plan</span></h2>
<h3 class='sec-h3'>Pre-migration</h3>
<p>- Extract source record counts per object/table</p>
<p>- Run duplicate detection queries (accounts by name+city, vehicles by registration)</p>
<p>- Validate all required fields are populated (Name, Registration_Number__c, Start_Date__c, etc.)</p>
<p>- Check referential integrity: all parent IDs exist in source (client_id, vehicle_id, etc.)</p>
<p>- Validate date formats can be parsed (YYYY-MM-DD or DD/MM/YYYY)</p>
<p>- Validate picklist values exist in target org (run picklist value comparison script)</p>
<p>- Check for future dates in historical records (Incident_Date__c, Activity_Date__c)</p>
<p>- Validate email and phone number formats</p>
<p>- Check for negative currency values</p>
<p>- Validate date ranges (Start &lt; End for contracts and policies)</p>
<p>- Generate pre-migration data quality report with all flagged issues</p>
<h3 class='sec-h3'>Post-migration</h3>
<p>- Record count verification per object</p>
<p>- Account lookup resolution on Contacts</p>
<p>- Vehicle lookup resolution on Rental Contracts</p>
<p>- Client lookup resolution on Rental Contracts</p>
<p>- Vehicle lookup resolution on Maintenance Activities</p>
<p>- Sinistre parent lookup resolution on Involved Parties</p>
<p>- Registration number uniqueness on Vehicles</p>
<p>- Policy number uniqueness on Insurance Policies</p>
<p>- Invoice billing period uniqueness per contract</p>
<p>- Validate contract status calculation</p>
<p>- Validate insurance policy status calculation</p>
<p>- Field value spot check - Accounts</p>
<p>- Field value spot check - Vehicles</p>
<p>- Field value spot check - Rental Contracts</p>
<p>- Verify Total_Maintenance_Cost__c rollup on Vehicles</p>
<p>- Verify Claims aggregation on Insurance Policies</p>
<p>- Validate no orphaned child records</p>
<p>- Verify RecordType assignment</p>
<p>- Verify RecordType assignment for Contacts</p>
<p>- Check for data quality flags</p>
<h2 id='sub-9-7' class='sec-h2'><span>9.7 Rollback Strategy</span></h2>
<table class='tbl tbl-kv'>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Approach</td>
<td>Delete by Migration_Batch__c tag in reverse dependency order (children before parents). Use Data Loader delete operation with SOQL queries.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Steps</td>
<td>• 1. BACKUP: Export all migrated records to CSV before rollback (WHERE Migration_Batch__c = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD') <span class='dot'>·</span> 2. Delete Involved_Party__c WHERE Migration_Batch__c = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' (Master-Detail child of Sinistre__c) <span class='dot'>·</span> 3. Delete Mileage_Readingc WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 4. Delete Problem_Reportc WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 5. Delete Invoicec WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 6. Delete Sinistrec WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 7. Delete Maintenance_Activityc WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 8. Delete Rental_Contractc WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 9. Delete Insurance_Policyc WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 10. Delete Vehiclec WHERE Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 11. Delete Contact WHERE Migration_Batch__c = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 12. Delete Account WHERE Migration_Batch__c = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' <span class='dot'>·</span> 13. Verify record counts return to pre-migration state: SELECT COUNT() FROM {Object} for each object <span class='dot'>·</span> 14. Clear External ID fields if full rollback (optional): Update Legacy_*_Id__c fields to NULL on any remaining records <span class='dot'>·</span> 15. Document rollback in Migration_Log__c with reason, timestamp, and record counts deleted</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Safeguard</td>
<td>All migrated records tagged with Migration_Batchc = 'LOGIFLEET_INITIAL_LOAD' and Migration_Datec = {load_date} for traceability. Create custom fields on all objects: Migration_Batchc (Text 100), Migration_Datec (DateTime), Data_Quality_Issue__c (Text 255).</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
