<h2 id='sub-9-10' class='sec-h2'><span>9.10 Post</span> <em class='brass'>Migration Tasks</em></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>Task</strong></th>
<th><strong>Description</strong></th>
<th><strong>Timing / Owner</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Trigger rollup flows for aggregated fields</strong></td>
<td>Manually trigger or schedule flows to calculate Vehiclec.Total_Maintenance_Costc and Insurance_Policyc.Total_Claims_Countc based on migrated child records</td>
<td>Immediately after Phase 4 migration completion <em>Data Migration Specialist</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Activate scheduled flows</strong></td>
<td>Activate scheduled flows for contract status updates, invoice generation, policy expiration alerts, maintenance reminders (currently inactive during migration)</td>
<td>After all validation passes and before go-live <em>Salesforce Administrator</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Data quality cleanup</strong></td>
<td>Review all records flagged with Data_Quality_Issue__c and resolve manually (invalid emails, missing driver licenses, mileage anomalies)</td>
<td>Week 1-2 post-migration <em>Business Users + Admin</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Remove migration custom fields (optional)</strong></td>
<td>After 90-day stabilization period, consider removing Migration_Batchc, Migration_Datec, Legacy_*_Id__c fields if no longer needed. Keep External IDs if ongoing integration requires them.</td>
<td>90 days post-migration <em>Salesforce Administrator</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Archive source system data</strong></td>
<td>Export final source system data to secure archive. Decommission legacy system per IT policy.</td>
<td>After 30-day parallel run validation <em>IT Operations</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Update integration endpoints</strong></td>
<td>Configure mobile app and accounting system to point to production Salesforce org. Test all integration flows end-to-end.</td>
<td>Go-live day <em>Integration Developer</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>User training on migrated data</strong></td>
<td>Conduct training sessions showing users where to find migrated historical data, how to interpret legacy IDs, and data quality flags</td>
<td>Week before go-live <em>Training Team</em></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
